From e318875e8f5f8a02f3cc551d36328fbea415d90c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: SlayZone Dev <dev@slayzone.local>
Date: Sat, 18 Apr 2026 17:17:38 +0200
Subject: slayzone: Phase 5.2 10-slot placeholder grid + PlaceholderUI
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds chrome://slayzone-placeholder/<region> WebUI (path-based routing —
query strings get rejected by the chrome:// router on some builds and the
default WebUIDataSource CSP blocks inline scripts, so the region id lives
in the path and HTML is interpolated server-side).

SlayzoneBrowserView hosts a 10-slot BoxLayoutView grid
(shell/tabbar/projects/tasklist/sidebar/taskheader/browserchrome/terminal/
tools/statusbar). Each WebView loads chrome://slayzone-placeholder/<id>.
The region container is added as a later sibling of BrowserView's children
and sized from OnBoundsChanged — it overlays upstream chrome in paint order,
which avoids fighting BrowserViewTabbedLayoutImpl invariants that require
contents_container_ to stay visible + parented.

Placeholder host is listed in ChromeURLHosts() alongside slayzone-shell so
chrome://chrome-urls/ enumerates it.
